  <div class="container" style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;padding:2rem 1.5rem 4rem">
    <article class="article-content">
      <h1>Best VPN for China & eSIM Guide 2026: How to Stay Connected</h1>

      <p><strong>The Great Firewall is no joke.</strong> Google, Gmail, Instagram, WhatsApp, Facebook, YouTube, Twitter/X, Netflix — all blocked the moment you land. And you can't download a VPN after arrival because the airport WiFi requires a Chinese phone number to log in. Let's make sure you're set up <em>before</em> takeoff.</p>

      <p>This guide covers three approaches, from easiest to most flexible. Pick the one that fits your trip.</p>

      <nav aria-label="Table of Contents">
        <h2>📋 In This Guide</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><a href="#quick-pick">Quick Pick: What Should I Use?</a></li>
          <li><a href="#esim">Option 1: eSIM — Easiest for Short Trips</a></li>
          <li><a href="#vpn">Option 2: VPN — Most Flexible for Longer Stays</a></li>
          <li><a href="#localsim">Option 3: Local SIM + VPN Combo</a></li>
          <li><a href="#banned">VPNs That Don't Work in China</a></li>
          <li><a href="#setup">Pre-Flight Checklist</a></li>
